Yesterday, Suzanne and I had the opportunity to celebrate the ribbon cutting ceremony for the Herbert Hoover Dike! We are so excited that this project is complete and the safety it will provide for the surrounding communities! Although exciting, we must remember our mission that a higher dike cannot mean higher destructive water levels that hurt the much needed filter grasses and habitat. We have to continue to fight to #SaveLakeO! #SlowTheFlow Please Follow @anglersforlakeo to help protect her! 🙏

What I’ve learned over the years is that you can’t let one day define your season. Today was tough…I never got it going all day. What an intense week at the St. Lawrence! It was all or nothing and I gave it everything I had. Even with limited practice, I found a promising area but came up short in the end finishing 10th. Yet, there's a glimmer of hope with three more open tournaments to go to sneak in the Bassmaster Classic. 

I want to thank my Lord and Savior Jesus for allowing me to live my dream and support my family while doing it. Big LOVE to my family—Suzanne, Hilary, Amelia, Reed, Jacob and the rest of family for the prayers and endless support. Can't forget my incredible sponsors who have my back, on and off the water. I've got the best sponsors in the game, no doubt. Macoy and Dylan, your skills are top-notch, and you guys are instrumental in this journey.

And last but never least, a massive thank you to the fans who fuel my drive every time I hit the water. While the Elite series closes for the year, we've got some exciting stuff coming up: Team USA BASS Pan-Am in Arkansas and the World Championships in Portugal. Let’s keep the momentum going!
